cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY

The paper deals with multi-agent reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of deep neural networks in the proposed algorithm suggests that it belongs to the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The focus on multi-agent systems and communication mechanisms suggests that it could also belong to "cs.MA" (Multi-Agent Systems). The use of reinforcement learning and the optimization of policies suggests that it could belong to "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). The application of the algorithm to non-stationary environments suggests that it could belong to "cs.RO" (Robotics) or "cs.SY" (Systems and Control).
